
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `aptdcon` baraye modiriat dastresi be Internet az tarigh ravesh-haye apt (Advanced Package Tool) be kar miravad. Ba estefade az in dastoor, shoma mitavanid tarfik-haye dastresi ra tasim konid, mesle ijade mahdoodiat dar download ya update kardane package-ha.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `aptdcon --available`  --> 📦 List kardane tamame package-haye ghabele dastresi baraye download va nasb.
    🔹 `aptdcon --download-only package_name`  --> 📥 Fagat download kardane yek package be donbale ebtale nasb an.
    🔹 `aptdcon --show package_name`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh etelaat dar morede yek package khas.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ aptdcon --available

    🔹 Namayesh listi az tamame package-haye ghabele dastresi.

    $ aptdcon --download-only firefox

    🔹 Fagat package 'firefox' ra download mikonad bedoone nasb kardane an.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ aptdcon --show vlc

    🔹 Namayesh etelaate tafsili dar morede package 'vlc' mesle version, andaze va tozihat.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `aptdcon` command is used to manage internet access using APT (Advanced Package Tool) methods. Using this command, you can configure traffic access, such as creating restrictions on downloading or updating packages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `aptdcon --available`  --> 📦 List all available packages for download and installation.
    🔹 `aptdcon --download-only package_name`  --> 📥 Only download a specific package without installing it.
    🔹 `aptdcon --show package_name`  --> ℹ️ Show information about a specific package.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ aptdcon --available

    🔹 Show a list of all available packages.

    $ aptdcon --download-only firefox

    🔹 Only downloads the 'firefox' package without installing it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ aptdcon --show vlc

    🔹 Shows detailed information about the 'vlc' package, such as version, size, and description.

